WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:06.963
Woman: I'm the person
who hit you. I'm so sorry.

00:07.007 --> 00:09.487
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:09.966 --> 00:13.056
Thanks so much for having us.
I'm Shanice, and this is Kiana.

00:13.100 --> 00:14.492
Mom, she's amazing.

00:14.536 --> 00:16.059
Darcy:
Eddie, this is Russ.

00:16.103 --> 00:17.756
Whoa. You didn't tell me
this guy's in a wheelchair.

00:17.800 --> 00:19.280
I may have to charge extra.

00:19.323 --> 00:21.195
Gary: I, uh,
can relate to the, uh...

00:21.238 --> 00:23.545
OCD-type tendencies.

00:23.588 --> 00:26.765
What would you want to say
to the man who assaulted you?

00:26.809 --> 00:28.898
And I think everyone should know
your name.

00:28.941 --> 00:30.291
It's Peter Benoit.

00:30.334 --> 00:31.814
Saunders: If I thought
we could get a conviction,

00:31.857 --> 00:33.468
it would be different.

00:33.511 --> 00:36.036
But I am worried about having
enough evidence in this case.

00:36.079 --> 00:38.690
You were pretty upset
the other day at the station.

00:38.734 --> 00:40.388
Next day,
this guy's in the hospital.

00:40.431 --> 00:42.085
Eventually,
he's gonna wake up,

00:42.129 --> 00:44.522
and when he does, he can tell us
himself what happened.

00:44.566 --> 00:45.828
And if he doesn't
wake up,

00:45.871 --> 00:47.917
that just makes things
a lot more complicated.

00:47.960 --> 00:57.187
♪♪

00:57.231 --> 01:06.849
♪♪

01:06.892 --> 01:08.503
Anna:
No. When I found him there,

01:08.546 --> 01:10.026
I barely even recognized him.

01:10.070 --> 01:12.594
I mean, it was really bad.

01:12.637 --> 01:14.900
♪♪

01:14.944 --> 01:18.687
The doctors say that we won't
know anything for a while.

01:18.730 --> 01:22.038
But I really appreciate you
checking in on me, Mara.

01:22.082 --> 01:24.127
I will. Bye.

01:24.171 --> 01:26.608
♪♪

01:26.651 --> 01:28.479
[ Sighs ]

01:28.523 --> 01:29.437
[ Knock on door ]

01:31.439 --> 01:33.615
Mrs. Benoit?
Yes.

01:33.658 --> 01:36.052
Craig Saunders
with the Brookline PD?

01:36.096 --> 01:38.098
I'm sorry to bother you,
but I have a few more questions.

01:38.141 --> 01:39.795
Yes, of course.

01:39.838 --> 01:42.972
Thank you. Um, did you
notice anything unusual

01:43.015 --> 01:46.062
in the weeks leading up
to your husband's attack?

01:46.106 --> 01:48.064
What do you mean?

01:48.108 --> 01:50.980
Just trying to cover
all the bases.

01:51.023 --> 01:53.678
But there were no signs
of forced entry,

01:53.722 --> 01:55.593
which gives us
reason to believe

01:55.637 --> 01:57.465
that your husband
might have known his assailant.

01:57.508 --> 01:59.119
No, that doesn't
make any sense.

01:59.162 --> 02:02.165
No one that knows Peter
would want to hurt him.

02:02.209 --> 02:04.211
You've never heard of any
students being upset with him?

02:04.254 --> 02:05.734
Of course not.

02:05.777 --> 02:07.475
Peter is
an incredible teacher.

02:07.518 --> 02:10.260
I mean, his students, they --

02:10.304 --> 02:11.696
they love him.

02:11.740 --> 02:15.222
He has changed
so many lives.

02:15.265 --> 02:18.921
I'm sure.

02:18.964 --> 02:21.445
But just take a minute
and think about it for me.

02:21.489 --> 02:24.796
Anything
out of the ordinary?

02:24.840 --> 02:27.321
Um...

02:27.364 --> 02:31.368
I mean, I-I didn't think
anything of it at the time,

02:31.412 --> 02:35.242
but a few weeks ago, when I came
home late for choir practice,

02:35.285 --> 02:38.419
there -- there was a man
sitting in his car

02:38.462 --> 02:40.856
parked outside
of our house.

02:40.899 --> 02:44.381
Can you remember any details
about the man?

02:44.425 --> 02:46.209
What his car looked like?

02:46.253 --> 02:47.732
Uh, it was an S.U.V.

02:47.776 --> 02:50.518
Gray, I think.

02:50.561 --> 02:51.954
Dark gray.

02:54.217 --> 02:57.481
Oh, and he had a beard.

02:57.525 --> 03:00.441
If any of that is helpful.

03:00.484 --> 03:02.573
I think it might be.

03:07.404 --> 03:10.277
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

03:10.320 --> 03:11.582
Hey. What's up?

03:11.626 --> 03:13.889
Hey, pretty lady.
Whatcha doing tonight?

03:13.932 --> 03:17.284
Working, probably.
Let me check with my people.

03:17.327 --> 03:20.939
Alexa, what's on
my schedule tonight?

03:20.983 --> 03:22.245
Alexa:
Katherine, there's nothing

03:22.289 --> 03:24.378
on your schedule for tonight.

03:24.421 --> 03:26.641
Wow. She said that with
a little bit of judgment.

03:26.684 --> 03:28.730
[ Chuckles ]
That's because she doesn't know

03:28.773 --> 03:30.514
you're coming to Maggie's.

03:30.558 --> 03:32.342
We have a surprise for you.

03:32.386 --> 03:35.563
Gina, you know
I don't like surprises.

03:35.606 --> 03:36.999
Okay, okay,
I'll tell you,

03:37.042 --> 03:39.828
but you have to promise
to act surprised.

03:39.871 --> 03:41.612
We're throwing you
a divorce party.

03:41.656 --> 03:43.179
[ Squeals ]Divorce party.

03:43.223 --> 03:46.226
Is celebrating a failed marriage
really a thing?

03:46.269 --> 03:49.881
Honey, 12 years of marriage
is not a failure.

03:49.925 --> 03:52.667
That was an important
chapter of your life.

03:52.710 --> 03:55.365
And now that you are
starting a new one,

03:55.409 --> 03:57.759
we want to be there
to support you.

03:57.802 --> 03:59.369
And if we happen
to have some drinks

03:59.413 --> 04:01.066
and go out to a bar and meet
some cute men in the process,

04:01.110 --> 04:02.329
so be it.

04:02.372 --> 04:04.766
That's so thoughtful,
but really --

04:04.809 --> 04:06.507
Nope, not taking no
for an answer.

04:06.550 --> 04:07.943
Starts at 7:00.

04:07.986 --> 04:09.640
[ Sighs ]

04:09.684 --> 04:11.120
Alexa,
add to my schedule --

04:11.163 --> 04:13.992
"Divorce party,
7:00 P.M. tonight."

04:14.036 --> 04:16.299
Divorce party added
to your schedule.

04:16.343 --> 04:18.997
Divorce party! Whoo-whoo!

04:19.041 --> 04:21.783
They're having a divorce party.
That's pretty cold.

04:21.826 --> 04:25.613
Look, I get the excitement.
I went to one of those things.

04:25.656 --> 04:26.962
Hooked up with
the guest of honor

04:27.005 --> 04:30.008
in a Buffalo Wild Wings
storage closet.

04:30.052 --> 04:32.794
Luckily, she had
plenty of Wet-Naps

04:32.837 --> 04:34.404
to clean up my hot sau--

04:34.448 --> 04:36.885
Nope. No. No.

04:36.928 --> 04:39.714
Check swing. Self-correcting.
I'm a gentleman.

04:39.757 --> 04:41.498
Dude, what's gonna happen
when Ed finds out

04:41.542 --> 04:43.718
that Katherine's taking
a victory lap for leaving him?

04:45.197 --> 04:47.417
♪♪

04:47.461 --> 04:48.462
[ Peter grunting ]

04:48.505 --> 04:49.550
Get off!Gary: Shut up!

04:49.593 --> 04:50.855
Get off!
Get off of me!

04:50.899 --> 04:52.379
Help!

04:52.422 --> 04:54.119
Help me! Somebody!Rome: Mendez, you still there?

04:54.163 --> 04:55.295
I'm worried about Ed, bro.

04:55.338 --> 04:57.209
Yeah. Yeah, man.

04:57.253 --> 05:00.082
Yeah, I'm here.
Uh, it's a good point.

05:00.125 --> 05:04.086
I know I can't afford to send
him back to rehab, so, uh,

05:04.129 --> 05:07.045
we're not gonna
let him find out, okay?

05:07.089 --> 05:10.962
Luckily, we got the Bruins game
to distract him.

05:11.006 --> 05:13.443
Yes! Last game we get to watch
at your place.

05:13.487 --> 05:15.924
It's the end of an era.
So what I've done is,

05:15.967 --> 05:18.361
I've gotten us some Slim Jims,
some foot-longs,

05:18.405 --> 05:20.494
hot pretzels which may or
may not be from last season,

05:20.537 --> 05:22.104
just like the Garden.

05:22.147 --> 05:24.802
As long as nobody
pees in my sink.

05:24.846 --> 05:26.630
I believe it was you
who did that.

05:26.674 --> 05:29.024
Yeah, but that was before
I learned how to self-correct.

05:29.067 --> 05:30.678
Hockey, baby!

05:30.721 --> 05:32.070
Eddie:
The way she was looking at me,

05:32.114 --> 05:35.378
I figured it had to be
the woman who hit me.

05:35.422 --> 05:38.250
And it turns out she was
just a fan of my band.

05:38.294 --> 05:39.861
Whoa, wait.
You were in a band?

05:39.904 --> 05:41.123
Is that the same band

05:41.166 --> 05:42.994
you mention like five times
every session?

05:43.038 --> 05:44.735
[ Chuckles ]

05:44.779 --> 05:46.041
I know
she works at Halpert's.

05:46.084 --> 05:48.565
It's only a matter of time
before I find her.

05:48.609 --> 05:51.307
And when you do,
what are you gonna say?

05:51.351 --> 05:53.440
That she ruined my life.

05:53.483 --> 05:55.572
That I threw away
11 years of sobriety

05:55.616 --> 05:57.226
because of what she did.

05:57.269 --> 05:58.358
Then what?

05:58.401 --> 06:01.839
That my marriage imploded,

06:01.883 --> 06:04.494
and my poor son
has to shuttle between houses.

06:04.538 --> 06:05.974
I barely get to see him.

06:06.017 --> 06:07.279
Then what?

06:07.323 --> 06:09.107
Dude, what do you
want from me?

06:09.151 --> 06:10.326
I just want to know
what you're gonna say

06:10.370 --> 06:11.588
that's going to
reverse everything

06:11.632 --> 06:15.418
and magically get you
out of that chair.

06:15.462 --> 06:17.377
Believe me,
I get your anger.

06:17.420 --> 06:20.858
After I fell off that ladder,
oh, I was mad at everybody.

06:20.902 --> 06:24.296
The E.R. doctor who told me my
pain would only last a few days.

06:24.340 --> 06:26.255
My girlfriend for never
turning off that damn light.

06:26.298 --> 06:28.170
But ultimately,

06:28.213 --> 06:30.825
I realized I couldn't
keep living "B.C."

06:30.868 --> 06:31.956
"B.C."?

06:32.000 --> 06:34.568
Before Chair.

06:34.611 --> 06:38.136
You have every right
to be pissed off.

06:38.180 --> 06:42.967
But obsessing about it like this
is keeping you in the past.

06:43.011 --> 06:46.231
I mean, that and your obsession
with Axe body spray.

06:46.275 --> 06:47.581
Let's go, stinky.

06:47.624 --> 06:49.452
Time to get beat
by a quadriplegic.

06:50.758 --> 06:52.194
Again!

06:52.237 --> 06:55.197
♪♪

06:55.240 --> 06:56.459
[ Maggie and Sophie grunting ]

06:56.503 --> 06:59.767
Maggie: You get it?Uh, nope. Little higher.

06:59.810 --> 07:01.812
I knew I should have
asked Theo to help me.

07:01.856 --> 07:05.337
Oh, wow.
Short jokes, seriously?

07:05.381 --> 07:07.905
You clearly lived with Gary
for too long.

07:07.949 --> 07:09.516
Oh --

07:09.559 --> 07:11.996
Ooh.[ Both laugh ]

07:12.040 --> 07:13.433
Ah, there we go.

07:14.869 --> 07:16.479
[ Both sigh ]

07:16.523 --> 07:22.180
♪♪

07:22.224 --> 07:24.792
I'm surprised you
didn't ask your friend
Tennille to help you.

07:24.835 --> 07:26.228
From what I recall,
she's pretty tall.

07:26.271 --> 07:28.099
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.275
But I think
she's pretty busy

07:30.319 --> 07:33.496
getting ready
to go off to college.

07:33.540 --> 07:36.456
And you've been feeling
a little left out?

07:39.110 --> 07:41.156
Well, I...

07:41.199 --> 07:42.940
saw these IG posts
last night

07:42.984 --> 07:45.073
where bunch of kids
from my class

07:45.116 --> 07:47.554
were at this huge party.

07:47.597 --> 07:51.079
Maybe they just forgot
to invite me, or...

07:51.122 --> 07:53.081
you know, maybe they thought
it'd be difficult

07:53.124 --> 07:55.910
to let loose around me
after everything that happened.

07:57.781 --> 07:59.348
But I can still be fun
at a party.

07:59.391 --> 08:01.655
Yeah, of course you can.

08:01.698 --> 08:04.309
Which is why
you are coming with me

08:04.353 --> 08:07.617
to Katherine's
divorce party tonight.

08:07.661 --> 08:10.228
Ooh.
[ Chuckles ] That --

08:10.272 --> 08:12.535
I don't know. That kind of seems
like an old person thing.

08:12.579 --> 08:13.797
Wow.

08:13.841 --> 08:15.364
Okay, so I'm short
andI'm old?

08:15.407 --> 08:17.322
Now you're definitely
coming with me.

08:17.366 --> 08:20.064
I have a TikTok,
so you know.

08:20.108 --> 08:22.197
But you shouldn't,
so you know.

08:22.240 --> 08:24.765
Hey.

08:24.808 --> 08:26.375
I am telling your mom.

08:26.418 --> 08:27.681
[ Chuckles ]

08:27.724 --> 08:28.986
[ Fan whirring ]

08:29.030 --> 08:30.422
Darcy: You guys
are gonna have so much fun.

08:30.466 --> 08:32.076
Now, be good, okay?Yeah.

08:32.120 --> 08:35.036
What is --Whoa, there he is!

08:35.079 --> 08:37.647
Welcome to hockey night,
my young friend.

08:37.691 --> 08:39.954
Looks like a tornado
came through here.

08:39.997 --> 08:42.870
Yeah, a tornado
from 1995.

08:42.913 --> 08:44.785
I hope Hootie and his Blowfish
are okay.

08:44.828 --> 08:47.657
Ha! Heh. Theo's in the back
with his dad,

08:47.701 --> 08:49.529
speaking of relics
from the '90s.

08:49.572 --> 08:52.053
Go announce your presence,
with authority!

08:52.096 --> 08:54.577
Hello, chaos.

08:54.621 --> 08:58.494
Believe it or not, I have
a very organized system, okay?

08:58.538 --> 09:01.584
Dump. Donate.

09:01.628 --> 09:03.934
Definitely going to Lenox.

09:03.978 --> 09:06.546
Tell you what, toss that nasty
thing in that donate box,

09:06.589 --> 09:08.852
and I'll drop everything off
on my way across town.

09:08.896 --> 09:10.332
Deal.

09:10.375 --> 09:12.421
But only because I know
that thanks to my donation,

09:12.464 --> 09:15.903
someone, somewhere will soon
know the joys of the sack.

09:17.513 --> 09:19.341
Boom. Sacked it.

09:19.384 --> 09:20.734
I'd literally do anything

09:20.777 --> 09:22.083
to stop you from saying
the word "sack."

09:22.126 --> 09:23.911
No can do. Sorry.

09:23.954 --> 09:25.260
It's boys' night here.

09:25.303 --> 09:26.696
Coming up with cool names
for our junk

09:26.740 --> 09:28.437
is kind of our whole thing.

09:28.480 --> 09:31.527
Sounds fun, but not as fun
as our divorce party.

09:31.571 --> 09:34.617
Shh, shh. Okay.
Alright. I, uh --

09:34.661 --> 09:37.838
I don't know
if Ed is ready to hear

09:37.881 --> 09:40.144
how Katherine
got her groove back.

09:40.188 --> 09:42.103
Ah. I get that.

09:42.146 --> 09:44.888
After Steven and I separated
and I started dating again,

09:44.932 --> 09:47.064
he was over
grabbing the last of his stuff,

09:47.108 --> 09:49.458
and he found some condoms
in a drawer,

09:49.501 --> 09:50.981
and he was
super uncomfortable.

09:51.025 --> 09:52.853
Eh, more or less uncomfortable
than I am right now

09:52.896 --> 09:53.897
just hearing about it?

09:53.941 --> 09:55.812
Oh, fair enough.

09:55.856 --> 09:58.075
I will take care of Katherine,
and you take care of Eddie.

09:58.119 --> 10:00.077
And if we all survive,
I'll meet you back here tonight.

10:00.121 --> 10:01.905
Mm.

10:01.949 --> 10:04.952
♪ I wanna go dancing
all night ♪

10:04.995 --> 10:06.606
Okay.

10:06.649 --> 10:07.781
Is that centered?Um, yep.

10:07.824 --> 10:09.434
Okay! It's 7:00!
You know Katherine.

10:09.478 --> 10:12.176
She's always on time.
Quiet. Quiet. Quiet.

10:12.220 --> 10:14.222
Nobody's talking
except you.

10:14.265 --> 10:15.527
Right.

10:15.571 --> 10:16.659
[ Knock on door ][ All gasp ]

10:16.703 --> 10:17.878
-Ooh. Okay. Okay.
-She's here. Okay.

10:19.314 --> 10:20.707
Come in!

10:20.750 --> 10:22.883
[ All chuckling ]

10:22.926 --> 10:25.059
Surprise!Surprise!

10:25.102 --> 10:26.800
Wow!

10:26.843 --> 10:29.585
What in the world
is going on?

10:29.629 --> 10:31.935
What are you guys
all up to?

10:31.979 --> 10:34.329
You told her.

10:34.372 --> 10:35.199
-I told her.
-Gina!

10:35.243 --> 10:36.766
[ All sighing ]

10:36.810 --> 10:39.377
I am dressed all wrong
for this, aren't I?

10:39.421 --> 10:41.684
Hey, it's not your fault.
Regina should have told you

10:41.728 --> 10:44.208
to come ready to go to the bar,
not pass the bar.

10:44.252 --> 10:46.558
[ Laughter ]It's fine.
I have a ton of tops

10:46.602 --> 10:48.996
if you want something
a little less "Rizzoli & Isles."

10:49.039 --> 10:50.737
[ Laughter ]Regina: Wow,
we roasting now?

10:50.780 --> 10:53.696
I think she looks great.

10:53.740 --> 10:56.568
And after one of my margaritas,
you will, too.

10:56.612 --> 10:58.353
That is, if you can think
at all.

10:58.396 --> 10:59.441
-Oh.
-Ooh.

10:59.484 --> 11:00.790
Ooh.

11:00.834 --> 11:03.358
Yes, please.[ Chuckles ]

11:03.401 --> 11:05.360
For you.
Oh.

11:05.403 --> 11:07.667
Okay, well, this is gonna be
better than I thought.Mm-hmm.

11:07.710 --> 11:09.190
Thanks, Gina.Of course, girl!

11:09.233 --> 11:11.409
I always make
unlimited virgin margaritas

11:11.453 --> 11:13.760
for our designated driver.

11:13.803 --> 11:15.631
Surprise.[ Door opens ]

11:15.675 --> 11:17.328
Surprise?
Am I too late?

11:19.113 --> 11:21.681
Shanice! No one told me
you were gonna come.

11:21.724 --> 11:24.292
I have been locked in a hotel
room with an 11-year-old

11:24.335 --> 11:25.772
every night for
two weeks straight.

11:25.815 --> 11:27.556
There's no way
I was missing this.

11:27.599 --> 11:30.994
[ Laughter ]

11:31.038 --> 11:32.604
Uh, you know what, Maggie?

11:32.648 --> 11:35.912
I think maybe I should get into
something a little more fun.

11:35.956 --> 11:38.219
[ Gasps ] Yes.Yes, right this way.

11:38.262 --> 11:40.351
Are we doing cleavage
or backless?

11:40.395 --> 11:42.223
I'll get my boob tape.[ Laughter ]

11:42.266 --> 11:44.529
Bob: Up next,
your Bruins face off against

11:44.573 --> 11:46.706
the Pittsburgh Penguins.Eddie:
Whoo! Here we go. Here we go!

11:46.749 --> 11:48.708
Okay, I'd like to propose
a toast, gentlemen.

11:48.751 --> 11:50.710
Tonight, we initiate
two new members

11:50.753 --> 11:52.494
into our brotherhood
of Bruins fans...

11:52.537 --> 11:55.105
Hear, hear!...which started 12 years ago

11:55.149 --> 11:56.890
with our friend Jon.

11:56.933 --> 11:58.413
Mm.

11:58.456 --> 12:00.632
And as we say goodbye
to this fine venue --

12:00.676 --> 12:02.765
Hello from Boston.Nope, down in front.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.158
Alright, let's go, B's!Here we go.

12:04.201 --> 12:05.376
Yeah,
I can drink to that!

12:05.420 --> 12:06.900
Alright, fellas, come on.

12:06.943 --> 12:08.597
Root beers up.

12:08.640 --> 12:11.513
Hey. Hey, there, Theo.

12:11.556 --> 12:13.080
Phone down, root beer up.

12:13.123 --> 12:14.124
-Sorry.
-Come on, kid.

12:14.168 --> 12:15.604
He was just
texting Kiana.

12:15.647 --> 12:18.128
Ooh. Who is Kiana?

12:18.172 --> 12:19.739
Oh, wait, wait,
Shanice's daughter?

12:19.782 --> 12:22.045
Wait a minute, does my little
man have his first crush?

12:22.089 --> 12:23.786
No. I-I-I don't.

12:23.830 --> 12:25.701
Alright, so,
it's Theo and Kiana?

12:25.745 --> 12:29.052
That means we got
"Thiana" or "Kio."

12:29.096 --> 12:30.880
Kio.Oh, you sound like
a cute, little car.

12:30.924 --> 12:32.229
Stop it![ Men chuckle ]

12:32.273 --> 12:33.840
T, it's okay,
we've all been there.

12:33.883 --> 12:35.058
We know what it's like.Yeah.

12:35.102 --> 12:36.494
