Good one!No! Okay? Just stop.

24:35.299 --> 24:36.562
Just -- Just...

24:36.605 --> 24:38.607
stop.

24:38.651 --> 24:41.436
♪ We live different round here,
sipping sangria ♪

24:41.480 --> 24:43.743
♪ Sangria, the way

24:43.786 --> 24:46.572
Bob: Bruins and the Pens
tied at 2.

24:46.615 --> 24:48.617
Come on, boys.
You got this.

24:48.661 --> 24:50.663
Greg: ...highs and lows
from the Bruins.

24:50.706 --> 24:53.361
Passing was crisp,
and that slapshot from Andre?

24:53.404 --> 24:54.797
Wow. Look out.

24:54.841 --> 24:58.279
Bruh, can you let it go?

24:58.322 --> 24:59.802
This our last time
to watch the Bruins

24:59.846 --> 25:01.456
before you move,
so why don't you come over here

25:01.500 --> 25:03.153
and sit down, watch the game
with your friend,

25:03.197 --> 25:04.415
and forget about
your stupid hat?

25:04.459 --> 25:05.982
It doesn't bring you luck.

25:06.026 --> 25:07.549
Doesn't even
look good on you.

25:07.593 --> 25:08.724
It's not just the hat.

25:08.768 --> 25:13.163
It's that Jon
gave me the hat.

25:13.207 --> 25:15.339
When I was
going through chemo,

25:15.383 --> 25:16.602
after I had lost my hair,

25:16.645 --> 25:20.083
and these very, very sexy brows
were gone.

25:22.259 --> 25:25.436
He was just trying to make me
feel comfortable, you know?

25:25.480 --> 25:26.568
Said if I was going to go,

25:26.612 --> 25:30.006
I was going to go
in a Bruins hat.

25:30.050 --> 25:32.705
"At least God will know
that you have good taste."

25:34.968 --> 25:36.970
I know it's not logical.
I just --

25:37.013 --> 25:38.841
I get this thought stuck
in my head sometimes

25:38.885 --> 25:40.103
that the only reason
I'm still here

25:40.147 --> 25:42.366
is because of
that stupid hat.

25:42.410 --> 25:44.281
Bob: Third period
is about to start.

25:44.325 --> 25:46.283
Okay. Alright. Down to center ice.

25:48.285 --> 25:49.635
Let's find your ugly hat.

25:49.678 --> 25:50.679
Where have you looked?

25:50.723 --> 25:52.638
Everywhere, literally.

25:52.681 --> 25:55.249
Including the box
labeled "Taxes."

25:55.292 --> 25:56.598
I should just
throw that stuff out

25:56.642 --> 25:57.991
or get a working
DVD player.

25:58.034 --> 26:00.123
Look, it's got to be here
somewhere, right?

26:00.167 --> 26:01.995
Couldn't just
up and walk out of your house.

26:02.038 --> 26:03.605
I'm telling you, dude,

26:03.649 --> 26:06.913
nothing has
left this place today.

26:06.956 --> 26:10.046
Except that box of stuff
Darcy took to donate.

26:10.090 --> 26:12.962
♪♪

26:13.006 --> 26:15.486
Hey, yo, Liam! Grab
a jerky stick and hit the head.

26:15.530 --> 26:17.010
Boys' night's
going on the road.

26:17.053 --> 26:19.229
I got the sticks!

26:19.273 --> 26:20.840
Let's go!

26:20.883 --> 26:22.668
♪♪

26:22.711 --> 26:24.757
[ Clears throat ]

26:24.800 --> 26:26.497
♪ Don't pray to God,
I pray to you ♪

26:26.541 --> 26:28.935
I come in peace.

26:28.978 --> 26:30.719
With drink.

26:30.763 --> 26:32.373
[ Door shuts ]

26:32.416 --> 26:34.723
[ Muffled music
continues playing ]

26:34.767 --> 26:36.638
You want to talk about --

26:36.682 --> 26:37.900
Me being
an insane person?

26:37.944 --> 26:40.729
You are not insane.

26:40.773 --> 26:44.472
You're just...divorced.

26:44.515 --> 26:45.995
Welcome to the club.

26:46.039 --> 26:48.345
[ Sighs ]

26:48.389 --> 26:51.131
It's all the -- it's all
the shoulds, you know?

26:51.174 --> 26:52.698
You shouldhave
a divorce party.

26:52.741 --> 26:55.744
You should be ready
to date again.

26:55.788 --> 27:00.270
I've been playing that game
my entire life.

27:00.314 --> 27:01.358
You know,
starting with my parents --

27:01.402 --> 27:02.882
You should get
perfect grades.

27:02.925 --> 27:06.102
You should go to
the best college.

27:06.146 --> 27:10.411
I swear, I want to tear
that word out of the dictionary.

27:10.454 --> 27:12.369
Believe me, I get it.

27:14.023 --> 27:15.982
Can I, um --

27:16.025 --> 27:17.897
Can I ask you something?

27:17.940 --> 27:20.639
Sure.

27:20.682 --> 27:22.945
How long
after your divorce

27:22.989 --> 27:26.253
until you were ready
to go out with a guy again?

27:30.736 --> 27:33.390
Three months.

27:33.434 --> 27:38.178
But you are allowed to do things
at your own pace.

27:38.221 --> 27:40.615
You are the only one
who'll know when you are ready.

27:43.226 --> 27:44.184
Thank you.

27:47.187 --> 27:48.928
Hurry up, Dad.
They close in 10 minutes.

27:51.017 --> 27:52.801
Whoa.
This place is huge.

27:52.845 --> 27:55.586
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:55.630 --> 27:56.979
How about we split up?

27:57.023 --> 27:58.285
Great idea.

28:00.940 --> 28:09.557
♪♪

28:09.600 --> 28:11.211
Woman: [ Over P.A. ]
Attention, Halpert's shoppers.

28:11.254 --> 28:12.734
The store will be closing soon.

28:12.778 --> 28:14.954
Please bring your items
to the register.

28:14.997 --> 28:22.962
♪♪

28:23.005 --> 28:30.752
♪♪

28:30.796 --> 28:38.499
♪♪

28:38.542 --> 28:40.457
I want to
ask you something.

28:40.501 --> 28:43.809
♪♪

28:43.852 --> 28:46.072
Dad, did you find it?

28:46.115 --> 28:52.469
♪♪

28:52.513 --> 28:58.824
♪♪

28:58.867 --> 29:01.000
What aisle
for the glitter?

29:02.741 --> 29:03.959
Um...

29:04.003 --> 29:06.527
Aisle 7.

29:06.570 --> 29:08.485
It's next to the glue.

29:08.529 --> 29:11.967
♪♪

29:12.011 --> 29:13.882
Let's go.

29:13.926 --> 29:21.585
♪♪

29:26.242 --> 29:28.810
Okay, I texted Gina

29:28.854 --> 29:32.640
and told them
to keep going without us.

29:32.683 --> 29:34.033
[ Gasps ]

29:34.076 --> 29:35.077
Yes.
Yeah.

29:35.121 --> 29:36.818
[ Chuckles ]

29:36.862 --> 29:38.864
[ Sighs ] Well,

29:38.907 --> 29:40.735
I guess my friends
were right.

29:40.779 --> 29:42.998
I really can't
have fun at a party.

29:45.827 --> 29:47.568
Yeah, I just --
I-I keep trying

29:47.611 --> 29:49.309
to move past
everything to do with Peter,

29:49.352 --> 29:52.268
and it somehow keeps
catching up to me again.

29:52.312 --> 29:56.925
I just -- I feel like
I can't escape it, and...

29:56.969 --> 29:58.666
it sucks.

30:01.016 --> 30:02.496
Getting over
something like this

30:02.539 --> 30:04.150
is never gonna be
a straight line.

30:04.193 --> 30:06.979
It's gonna ebb and flow.

30:07.022 --> 30:08.937
But you will be okay.

30:08.981 --> 30:11.635
I promise.

30:11.679 --> 30:13.420
Thanks.
Mm-hmm.

30:15.204 --> 30:16.684
Alright.

30:16.727 --> 30:19.905
Never have I ever...

30:19.948 --> 30:22.298
run into the wife
of the man who assaulted me

30:22.342 --> 30:26.476
in front of a convenience store
while on an ice run.

30:26.520 --> 30:29.175
[ Sighs ] Um...
Hmm.

30:29.218 --> 30:32.526
Uh, never have I ever...

30:32.569 --> 30:34.310
pretended to be happy

30:34.354 --> 30:37.052
for my ex-boyfriend's
new girlfriend when she tells me

30:37.096 --> 30:41.143
she's going to start trying
to get pregnant very, very soon.

30:41.187 --> 30:43.842
Maybe even trying right now.

30:43.885 --> 30:46.235
Hmm.

30:46.279 --> 30:47.802
Oh, my lie felt bigger.

30:47.846 --> 30:50.457
[ Both laugh ]

30:50.500 --> 30:53.068
Okay.
Never have I ever

30:53.112 --> 30:55.505
said thank you.

30:55.549 --> 30:57.551
To you.

30:57.594 --> 30:59.031
For never questioning
what happened to me

30:59.074 --> 31:02.121
from the first moment
I told you.

31:02.164 --> 31:04.297
Very lucky to have you
in my life.

31:04.340 --> 31:08.257
♪♪

31:08.301 --> 31:09.780
Cheers.
Cheers.

31:11.130 --> 31:12.392
Bro, where you taking us?Right here. Right here.

31:12.435 --> 31:14.742
This is where Darcy said
she dropped my stuff.

31:14.785 --> 31:17.919
No. No! No!

31:17.963 --> 31:19.573
Damn.

31:19.616 --> 31:21.227
Okay, okay.
We'll just come back tomorrow.

31:21.270 --> 31:22.619
What if it's
not here tomorrow?

31:22.663 --> 31:24.621
Oh, right. I forgot

31:24.665 --> 31:26.406
about the hordes of people
who go Dumpster-diving

31:26.449 --> 31:28.887
for moldy Bruins hats
at 3:00 in the morning.

31:28.930 --> 31:30.584
Now is not the time
for negativity, Rome.

31:30.627 --> 31:32.412
You are the king
of negativity!

31:32.455 --> 31:34.022
No, I am
the king of sarcasm.

31:34.066 --> 31:36.633
It is that subtle difference
that wins over the hearts --

31:36.677 --> 31:38.809
Whoa, whoa! Kid,
you don't want to go in there.

31:38.853 --> 31:40.986
I mean, you thought
Rome's jersey was bad --

31:41.029 --> 31:42.988
I need to get your hat.Oh, this is ridiculous.

31:43.031 --> 31:45.120
I'm going in there.
Yep. Okay.

31:45.164 --> 31:47.079
What are you doing?

31:47.122 --> 31:48.602
Gary: Ah, dude!Dude, give me a boost.

31:48.645 --> 31:50.082
Give me a boost, please.I'm not --

31:50.125 --> 31:51.953
Ow. Okay, I'm losing my grip.Liam, seriously, man!

31:51.997 --> 31:53.433
Ooh!Let's get out of here

31:53.476 --> 31:55.261
before Spider-Man
breaks a hip, okay?Ow.

31:55.304 --> 31:56.958
We'll come back tomorrow.

31:57.002 --> 31:58.525
No. No, I want to try.

31:58.568 --> 32:00.222
It's okay.

32:03.095 --> 32:04.183
Are you sure?

32:04.226 --> 32:05.575
[ Grunts ] Yeah.

32:05.619 --> 32:07.099
[ Door thumps ]

32:07.142 --> 32:09.405
You always got my back.

32:09.449 --> 32:11.320
Now I've got yours.

32:11.364 --> 32:15.063
♪♪

32:15.107 --> 32:17.544
Care...ful.

32:17.587 --> 32:24.203
♪♪

32:24.246 --> 32:26.074
It says
no mattresses, no TVs.

32:26.118 --> 32:28.381
Doesn't say anything
about donating children.

32:28.424 --> 32:35.605
♪♪

32:35.649 --> 32:38.130
Um, honey,
we're so sorry.

32:38.173 --> 32:41.133
Yeah, you -- you kept trying
to tell us and we didn't listen.

32:41.176 --> 32:45.615
No, I'm the one who's sorry
for snapping like that.

32:45.659 --> 32:48.270
I love you guys
for planning all this.

32:48.314 --> 32:49.968
And you areright.

32:50.011 --> 32:53.623
I do need to celebrate
this new chapter.

32:53.667 --> 32:57.627
But I need to do it
in the way that I want to,

32:57.671 --> 32:59.890
not the way that other people
think I should,

32:59.934 --> 33:03.677
even if those people
are my best friends.

33:03.720 --> 33:06.593
Whatever you want
sounds perfect to us.

33:06.636 --> 33:10.379
Well, I thought about that,
and what I want to do

33:10.423 --> 33:12.947
is kick your butts
at Flip Cup.

33:12.991 --> 33:15.080
[ Laughs ]
Well, I'm game.

33:15.123 --> 33:17.386
A little scared, but game.[ Giggling ]

33:17.430 --> 33:18.648
I'll get the cups.

33:18.692 --> 33:19.780
[ Rattling ]

33:19.823 --> 33:22.826
Hey, kid,
how you doing in there?

33:22.870 --> 33:24.263
Liam?

33:24.306 --> 33:25.699
Liam: I found the box!

33:25.742 --> 33:27.788
You did?Yeah, but...

33:29.181 --> 33:30.747
it's not in here.

33:30.791 --> 33:32.010
What?

33:32.053 --> 33:33.359
Your hat,
i-it's not in the box.

33:33.402 --> 33:36.318
I-I took everything out.

33:36.362 --> 33:38.016
[ Sighs ]
I'm really sorry.

33:40.409 --> 33:41.758
No, no, don't be sorry.

33:41.802 --> 33:43.586
Are you kidding me?
That was amazing.

33:43.630 --> 33:45.675
Besides, it's just a --
It's a stupid, old hat.

33:45.719 --> 33:48.678
[ Strained chuckle ]

33:48.722 --> 33:50.985
Maybe I...

33:51.029 --> 33:54.206
just have to face the fact
that things are changing.

33:54.249 --> 33:55.468
Maybe we all do, man.

33:57.339 --> 33:59.950
Liam:
[ Sighs ] I'm sorry.

33:59.994 --> 34:04.042
No, no, no. I got something
way better than a hat tonight.

34:04.085 --> 34:07.697
I got a kid willing to set aside
his own fears

34:07.741 --> 34:09.786
so that he could be there for me
no matter what.

34:11.745 --> 34:13.442
I love you, little man.

34:13.486 --> 34:15.053
♪♪

34:15.096 --> 34:16.532
Bring it in.

34:16.576 --> 34:20.449
♪♪

34:20.493 --> 34:23.670
You know, I did get one thing
when I was in that Dumpster.

34:23.713 --> 34:25.628
Hepatitis?

34:25.672 --> 34:26.977
[ Gasps ]

34:27.021 --> 34:28.414
The sack.

34:28.457 --> 34:31.156
The sack is back.Oh, man.

34:31.199 --> 34:33.854
The sack is back.

34:33.897 --> 34:35.116
Stop saying "sack."Liam, am I wrong,

34:35.160 --> 34:36.204
or is the sack back?

34:36.248 --> 34:37.988
The sack is back.Ha, ha, ha!

34:38.032 --> 34:40.687
♪♪

34:40.730 --> 34:42.863
So, let me
get this straight.

34:42.906 --> 34:44.734
Your friends
are leaving in an Uber,

34:44.778 --> 34:47.172
and you're doing the dishes
at someone else's house?

34:47.215 --> 34:49.087
Thought you weren't doing
"shoulds" anymore.

34:49.130 --> 34:50.610
I'm not.

34:50.653 --> 34:52.525
Doing dishes is my jam.

34:52.568 --> 34:56.529
An overly competitive,
dish-washing, Flip Cup champion?

34:56.572 --> 34:58.966
[ Chuckles ]You have many layers.

35:00.837 --> 35:03.710
Hey, thanks for
listening to me earlier.

35:03.753 --> 35:05.451
It really helps
to talk to someone

35:05.494 --> 35:07.540
who's been through
the same thing.

35:09.933 --> 35:12.719
I wasn't totally honest
with you before.

35:15.069 --> 35:19.117
It wasn't a guy that I dated
right after my divorce.

35:19.160 --> 35:21.728
It was a woman.

35:21.771 --> 35:24.296
I don't share that
with everyone,

35:24.339 --> 35:26.559
which is why I didn't drink
during "Never Have I Ever."

35:28.343 --> 35:30.476
But I feel like
I can trust you.

35:30.519 --> 35:32.652
Of course you can.

35:34.436 --> 35:37.439
Do you keep it a secret
because of your career?

35:37.483 --> 35:39.049
Partly.

35:39.093 --> 35:42.227
But the truth
is way less exciting.

35:42.270 --> 35:45.273
It's my parents.

35:45.317 --> 35:47.580
They would not understand,

35:47.623 --> 35:49.843
and they're at
that stage of life

35:49.886 --> 35:53.194
where it just isn't
worth messing with.

35:53.238 --> 35:55.414
Oh, are you kidding me? I mean,
my mom doesn't even like it

35:55.457 --> 35:56.763
when I wear pants.

35:56.806 --> 35:58.634
[ Both chuckle ]

35:58.678 --> 36:00.114
[ Laughs ]

36:00.158 --> 36:01.811
It's not thatfunny,
is it?

36:01.855 --> 36:03.596
You have suds
on your face.

36:03.639 --> 36:06.207
I was talking this whole time
with suds on my face?

36:06.251 --> 36:08.253
[ Laughs ] Here.Where?

36:08.296 --> 36:15.695
♪♪

36:15.738 --> 36:18.567
Okay, I think --
I think that's everything.

36:18.611 --> 36:21.831
Um, I-I got to call Theo
in a couple minutes

36:21.875 --> 36:23.181
to say good night.

36:23.224 --> 36:24.269
Yeah, and if I leave now,

36:24.312 --> 36:26.532
I can probably still
tuck Kiana in.

36:26.575 --> 36:28.490
This was really fun.

36:28.534 --> 36:30.231
I've always
used a dishwasher.

36:30.275 --> 36:31.754
Or someone has.

36:31.798 --> 36:33.191
[ Chuckles ]

36:33.234 --> 36:35.976
♪♪

36:40.415 --> 36:43.244
Bob: Try to rebound
from tonight's loss --

36:43.288 --> 36:46.421
Bruins lost.
I don't have my hat.

36:46.465 --> 36:49.207
Coincidence?
I think not.

36:49.250 --> 36:51.687
Hey, sorry about overreacting
about the game.

36:51.731 --> 36:52.862
Ah.

36:52.906 --> 36:55.430
No, it's just --
it's tough, you know,

36:55.474 --> 36:57.650
the thought that there are

36:57.693 --> 37:00.740
gonna be less nights
like tonight.

37:00.783 --> 37:04.613
You know,
I'mma miss you, man.

37:04.657 --> 37:06.702
Now, of course, there's some
things I'm gonna be cool
without, too, right?

37:06.746 --> 37:07.964
Like putting kids
in Dumpsters,

37:08.008 --> 37:09.662
starting fist fights
with white supremacists.

37:09.705 --> 37:11.925
One time.
I punched a racist one time --

37:11.968 --> 37:13.274
Don't say for me.For you.

37:13.318 --> 37:15.537
[ Both laugh ]

37:15.581 --> 37:18.627
[ Sighs ]

37:18.671 --> 37:22.805
You know,
until two years ago,

37:22.849 --> 37:24.851
my longest romantic
relationship

37:24.894 --> 37:26.983
was with a poster
of Kathy Ireland.

37:27.027 --> 37:28.898
[ Chuckles ]

37:28.942 --> 37:31.292
And now...

37:31.336 --> 37:34.643
I've got Darcy and Liam.

37:36.210 --> 37:40.301
And sometimes, I, uh...

37:40.345 --> 37:43.304
I feel like I don't
deserve any of it.

37:43.348 --> 37:45.567
Of course you deserve it.

37:45.611 --> 37:47.787
♪♪

37:47.830 --> 37:50.398
And seeing you tonight
with Liam was...

37:50.442 --> 37:52.792
♪♪

37:52.835 --> 37:55.534
You're gonna be an amazing dad,
Gary Mendez.

37:57.536 --> 37:59.668
And even if
you did lose that hat,

37:59.712 --> 38:02.192
I know
Jon would think so, too.

38:02.236 --> 38:05.761
♪♪

38:05.805 --> 38:07.110
Thanks, man.

38:07.154 --> 38:09.591
♪♪

38:09.635 --> 38:12.290
Now, can you do it
as a rap?

38:12.333 --> 38:13.334
Still don't like you.

38:13.378 --> 38:15.641
[ Chuckles ]

38:15.684 --> 38:18.992
♪♪

38:19.035 --> 38:20.602
On my mark, okay?

38:20.646 --> 38:22.300
Eddie:
Okay, speaker's ready.

38:22.343 --> 38:24.214
[ Exhales shakily ]

38:24.258 --> 38:25.912
[ Knock on door ]

38:29.176 --> 38:32.266
Theo?
What are you doing here?

38:32.310 --> 38:34.355
[ Through speaker ]
♪ Where am I supposed to be?♪

38:34.399 --> 38:38.098
♪ Washed up, pushed out
or on my feet♪

38:38.141 --> 38:43.233
♪ Tell me, is this a dream or
am I stuck in a movie scene? ♪

38:43.277 --> 38:45.584
[ Chuckles ]♪ Daily, lately

38:45.627 --> 38:50.937
♪ I'm spinning away so crazy,
so, baby, just take me ♪

38:50.980 --> 38:56.159
♪ I think I'm caught up
in the way I feel 'bout you ♪

38:56.203 --> 39:01.251
♪ I don't know how I can be
so drawn into you ♪

39:01.295 --> 39:06.692
♪ I think I'm fallin' in deep

39:06.735 --> 39:10.783
♪ I think I'm caught up
in the wave of you ♪

39:10.826 --> 39:13.829
[ Paint cracking ]♪ Of you, mm

39:13.873 --> 39:16.266
♪ Oh, upside-down

39:16.310 --> 39:17.964
[ Inhales deeply ]♪ I'm tip-toein' undersea

39:18.007 --> 39:20.967
Eddie:
[ Whispering ] You got this.

39:21.010 --> 39:22.447
I --

39:22.490 --> 39:25.014
I really like you.

39:25.058 --> 39:26.581
I really like you, too.

39:26.625 --> 39:29.192
♪ Caught up in the way
I feel 'bout you ♪

39:29.236 --> 39:31.194
Okay, bye.
Bye.

39:31.238 --> 39:33.414
♪ I don't know how I can be
so drawn into you ♪

39:33.458 --> 39:34.981
[ Eddie laughs ]

39:35.024 --> 39:38.680
You crushed it, kiddo!
